      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALFNALMA (8) is first up after tacking a Listed race three months ago but had very strong form prior including a Menangle win two back. Draws wide but will be ready to go off two trial wins and has a great record here, winning five of six attempts. MIKE ROSS NZ (6) was second-up last start and produced a better effort when runner-up from this barrier, beaten 1.4 metres. Has good statistics both here and at the distance and should be close to his peak now. MIKI BE GOOD (5) had a tough run when a beaten favourite in the city last time but was an easy winner in a good line-up prior so can bounce back. SHEZ SWEET LOUISE NZ (7) worked as a beaten favourite last time but was racing very consistently prior including a Blayney Cup win two back so is worth another chance.",
